node.text:
As we wrap up our theme of Food & Migration, Origins, and Seeds, I am sharing 5️⃣ fundamental things you need to know about seeds:

1. Seeds are the very essence of life, one of the main (hidden) pillars of our civilization, eons of ecosystem's evolution and memory encoded in DNA.

2. The richness of global "heritage" owes more to intercontinental seed and cultural exchange (and travel technologies) than to any other factors. Global food culture benefits from exchange and diversity.

3. We are losing seed diversity at an alarming rate -wiping out thousands of years of agricultural curation and culture-  and we must act.

4. Seed-saving preserves our food culture, and the best form of seed saving is by planting them! 

5. Biodiversity of seeds is essential in our efforts for a regenerative world, for a resilient, abundant and fair food system, and to accomplish the SDGs.

Please add to the list of what you think we should all know about seeds in the comments! ⬇️

🌱 Thank you to all of the people who contributed to the knowledge shared in these past months: @debora_fadul of @diacagt, Erick of @reisaedu, Edson of @senacri.gt, @isawstephen of @whetstonemagazine, @iluikamina of @kaalan_neek, @alejosses of @frito.lat, Alba Portillo of @redguardianesdesemillasdevid, and all my dear @charlesxmichelpatrons.

Stay tuned! Our next big theme will be on #PleasureActivism ✊🏽🤤

In this Live, we talk about seed exchange, evolution of culture, the importance of collect, redefining locality and more. 

Add your reflections in the comments! ⬇️

And as mentioned, make sure to check out @netflix’s #highonthehog with my friend @isawstephen!

node.text:
The #FoodPainting in this photo from my last #LiveCookingClass with @charlesxmichelpatrons was an effort to combine purpose and pleasure.

I truly believe our activism doesn’t have to be a painstaking climb, rather it can (and should?) be a growthful journey of joy and prosperity. 

This Saturday September 4th at 15:00 UTC , we’ll continue the conversation on "Food & Pleasure," this time specifically around pleasure in activism. 

In what ways do you combine purpose and pleasure? Let me know in the comments below. ⬇️ And please feel free to ask me a question  or share your thoughts on this topic… I may reflect on it on Saturday! 

#foodandpleasure #pleasureactivism #consciouseating #moderation #foodeducation #foodactivism #adriannemareebrown #inspo #liveqanda
______

El “Food Painting” (pintura con alimentos) en esta foto de mi última #ClasedeCocinaenVivo con @charlesxmichelpatrons fue un esfuerzo para combinar propósito y placer. Estoy convencido que el activismo no tiene que ser una batalla de sacrificios, sino que puede (y debe?) ser un camino de crecimiento, alegría y prosperidad.

“Sola dosis facit venenum” /// “The dose makes the poison” 🌿💊 a condensed version of chemist and philosopher Paracelsus’ maxim, “All things are poison, and nothing is without poison; the dosage alone makes it so a thing is not a poison.”

Curious what your thoughts are on guilty pleasures! Let me know in the comments below. ⬇️

"Sola dosis facit venenum" /// "La dosis hace el veneno" 🌿💊 una versión condensada de la máxima del químico y filósofo Paracelso, "Todas las cosas son veneno, y nada es libre de veneno; la dosis sola hace que una cosa sea o no veneno."

Me da curiosidad saber qué opinan de los (mal llamados) "pecados" de placer (o 'placeres culpables' como se les dice en inglés). Comenten aquí abajo! ⬇️

Few things give a greater pleasure than eating food from the garden just after picking it. 

But growing your own food - even just a part of it - is not just nice and sweet. It's tuning back into who we are as humans. It's reducing stress on natural environments. It's a political act. 

*Rather than taking the tip off, I ended up eating the whole strawberry after I returned the worms to the soil. #delicious

#foodandpleasure #pleasureactivism #strawberries #multisensory #joyequalschange #foodeducation #foodactivist #slowfood #conscious #jointheregeneration #sensory #regeneration #regenerativeagriculture #consciouseating #consciousconsumer #consciousliving #sustainableliving #sustainablefood #zerowasteliving  #realfood #climateaction #eatugly #plantbasedfood #foodforthought #canyouhearthecrunch #foodasmr #lifecycle #gardengrown
......

Pocas cosas me dan más placer que comer alimentos del jardín justo después de cosecharlos. 

Pero cultivar sus propios alimentos -así sea solo una parte- no es sólo agradable y dulce. Es volver a sintonizarnos con lo que somos como humanos. Es reducir nuestro impacto sobre ecosistemas naturales. Es un acto político. 

*En lugar de quitar la punta, acabé comiendo la fresa entera después de devolver los gusanos a la tierra #delicia

❓✨ Next LIVE Q&A 🌈❓
Theme: Food & Pleasure // Saturday, August 7th at 15:00 UTC 

Over the next couple of months, I intend to explore the topic of #Food & #Pleasure with you, both here on Insta and on my #Patreon. Why? Because many of us have forgotten or have been deconditioned to experience the joys of growing, cooking, eating, and sharing food. Further, our pleasure mechanisms are often tapped into to incite unconscious consumption of unhealthy ingredients for us, and the planet. 

How can we design for pleasure AND health? What can the perceptual mechanisms of pleasure in food inform our thinking, and our daily habits? How can we use #foodporn to incite healthier habits? How about food ASMR for wellbeing (instead of binge-eating #mukbang)? How could policy makers get involved in using pleasure (instead of prevention/repression) towards healthier habits?

The only way we will make mass systemic change is if we enjoy the process. So let's start by understanding pleasure #foodjustice #foodforchange

We'll start the conversation in our Live Q&A this Saturday. I imagine you've got some JUICY questions on this topic, so please ask them in the comments below! 🍕

After the Insta Q&A, join me for a 30min intimate "Patrons Only" Q&A on a dedicated Zoom call. Sign up on Patreon to join! [Link in my bio]
